    <h2>Fun Facts About F1</h2>
    <div class="fact">
        <strong>Fact 1:</strong> The fastest F1 car ever recorded was the 2005 Ferrari F2004, which reached a top speed of 372 km/h (231 mph) at the Italian Grand Prix.
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
        <strong>Fact 2:</strong> F1 cars can go from 0 to 100 km/h in just 2.6 seconds!
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
        <strong>Fact 3:</strong> The Monaco Grand Prix is one of the most prestigious races in the F1 calendar, known for its challenging street circuit.
    </div>
    <div class="fact">
        <strong>Fact 4:</strong> F1 drivers experience up to 5 G-forces while cornering at high speeds.
